{"id":"328434101_ANR_Aspect-based_Neural_Recommender","abstract":"Textual reviews, which are readily available on many e-commerce and review websites such as Amazon and Yelp, serve as an invaluable source of information for recommender systems. However, not all parts of the reviews are equally important, and the same choice of words may reflect a different meaning based on its context. In this paper, we propose a novel end-to-end Aspect-based Neural Recommender (ANR) to perform aspect-based representation learning for both users and items via an attention-based component. Furthermore, we model the multi-faceted process behind how users rate items by estimating the aspect-level user and item importance by adapting the neural co-attention mechanism. Our proposed model concurrently address several shortcomings of existing recommender systems, and a thorough experimental study on 25 benchmark datasets from Amazon and Yelp shows that ANR significantly outperforms recently proposed state-of-the-art baselines such as DeepCoNN, D-Attn and ALFM.","authors":["Jin Yao Chin","Kaiqi Zhao","Shafiq Joty","Gao Cong"],"meta":["October 2018","DOI:10.1145/3269206.3271810","Conference: the 27th ACM International Conference"],"references":["318915371_Aspect_Based_Recommendations_Recommending_Items_with_the_Most_Valuable_Aspects_Based_on_User_Reviews","312492565_Joint_Deep_Modeling_of_Users_and_Items_Using_Reviews_for_Recommendation","303750057_Hierarchical_Co-Attention_for_Visual_Question_Answering","284576917_Glove_Global_Vectors_for_Word_Representation","280105148_Collaborative_Deep_Learning_for_Recommender_Systems","278734421_Image-Based_Recommendations_on_Styles_and_Substitutes","266658499_Explicit_factor_models_for_explainable_recommendation_based_on_phrase-level_sentiment_analysis","265554557_Collaborative_Deep_Learning_for_Recommender_Systems","265252627_Neural_Machine_Translation_by_Jointly_Learning_to_Align_and_Translate","257882504_Distributed_Representations_of_Words_and_Phra